block vars
  - var activeLink = 'vue';
  - var title = 'Toolbar Vue Component | Framework7 Documentation';

block content
  .docs-wrap
    .docs-nav
      include ../_docs-vue-menu
    .docs-content
      h1 Toolbar Vue Component
      p Toolbar is a fixed (with Fixed and Through layout types) area at the bottom of a screen that contains navigation elements. Toolbar does not have any parts, just plain links inside
      p Toolbar Vue component represents <a href="../docs/toolbar.html">Toolbar</a> component.
      h2 Usage examples
      pre
        code
          :code
            <f7-toolbar>
              <f7-link>Left Link</f7-link>
              <f7-link>Right Link</f7-link>
            </f7-toolbar>
      p Renders to:
      pre
        code
          :code
            <div class="toolbar">
              <div class="toolbar-inner">
                <a href="#" class="link">Left Link</a>
                <a href="#" class="link">Right Link</a>
              </div>
            </div>
      h4 Bottom Toolbar (Affects Material Theme only)
      pre
        code
          :code
            <f7-toolbar bottom>
              <f7-link>Left Link</f7-link>
              <f7-link>Right Link</f7-link>
            </f7-toolbar>
      p Renders to:
      pre
        code
          :code
            <div class="toolbar toolbar-bottom">
              <div class="toolbar-inner">
                <a href="#" class="link">Left Link</a>
                <a href="#" class="link">Right Link</a>
              </div>
            </div>
      h4 Tabbar
      pre
        code
          :code
            <f7-toolbar tabbar>
              <f7-link tab-link="#tab1">Tab 1</f7-link>
              <f7-link tab-link="#tab2">Tab 2</f7-link>
            </f7-toolbar>
      p Renders to:
      pre
        code
          :code
            <div class="toolbar tabbar">
              <div class="toolbar-inner">
                <a href="#" class="tab-link" data-tab="#tab1">Tab 1</a>
                <a href="#" class="tab-link" data-tab="#tab2">Tab 2</a>
              </div>
            </div>
      h4 Tabbar With Labels
      pre
        code
          :code
            <f7-toolbar tabbar labels>
              <f7-link icon="icon-1" text="Tab 1" tab-link="#tab1"></f7-link>
              <f7-link icon="icon-2" text="Tab 2" tab-link="#tab2"></f7-link>
            </f7-toolbar>
      p Renders to:
      pre
        code
          :code
            <div class="toolbar tabbar tabbar-labels">
              <div class="toolbar-inner">
                <a href="#" class="tab-link" data-tab="#tab1">
                  <i class="icon icon-1"></i>
                  <span class="tabbar-label">Tab 1</span>
                </a>
                <a href="#" class="tab-link" data-tab="#tab1">
                  <i class="icon icon-2"></i>
                  <span class="tabbar-label">Tab 2</span>
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
      h4 Scrollable Tabbar
      pre
        code
          :code
            <f7-toolbar tabbar scrollable>
              <f7-link tab-link="#tab1">Tab 1</f7-link>
              <f7-link tab-link="#tab2">Tab 2</f7-link>
            </f7-toolbar>
      p Renders to:
      pre
        code
          :code
            <div class="toolbar tabbar tabbar-scrollable">
              <div class="toolbar-inner">
                <a href="#" class="tab-link" data-tab="#tab1">Tab 1</a>
                <a href="#" class="tab-link" data-tab="#tab2">Tab 2</a>
              </div>
            </div>
      h2 Slots
      p Toolbar Vue component (&lt;f7-toolbar&gt;) has additional slots for custom elements:
      ul
        li <b>before-inner</b> - element will be inserted right before &lt;div class="toolbar-inner"&gt; element
        li <b>after-inner</b> - element will be inserted right after &lt;div class="toolbar-inner"&gt; element
      pre
        code
          :code
            <f7-toolbar>
              <div slot="before-inner">Before Inner</div>
              <div slot="after-inner">After Inner</div>
              <f7-link>Left Link</f7-link>
              <f7-link>Right Link</f7-link>
            </f7-toolbar>
      p Renders to:
      pre
        code
          :code
            <div class="toolbar">
              <div>Before Inner</div>
              <div class="toolbar-inner">
                <a href="#" class="link">Left Link</a>
                <a href="#" class="link">Right Link</a>
              </div>
              <div>After Inner</div>
            </div>
      h2 Properties
      table.params-table
        thead
          tr
            th Prop
            th Type
            th Description
        tbody
          tr
            td bottom
            td boolean
            td Defines whether the Toolbar should be on bottom or not (Material theme only)
          tr
            td tabbar
            td boolean
            td Defines whether the Toolbar is also a <a href="../docs/tabbar.html">Tab Bar</a>
          tr
            td labels
            td boolean
            td Enables Tab Bar with labels (affects only when <code>tabbar: true</code>)
          tr
            td scrollable
            td boolean
            td Enables scrollable Tab Bar (affects only when <code>tabbar: true</code>)
          tr
            td theme
            td string
            td Toolbar theme color. One of <a href="../docs/color-themes.html">default colors</a>
          tr
            td layout
            td string
            td Toolbar layout theme. One of <a href="../docs/color-themes.html#layout-themes">default layout themes</a>